gitconfig

core.excludesFile defaults to $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/git/ignore. If $XDG_CONFIG/git/ignore is either not set or empty, $HOME/.config/git/ignore is used instead.
Place config entries local to the current environment in config__local. The global config will include it.


`git --list-cmds=main,others` list almost all subcommands excluding aliases.
Use this to decide alises.